  <bodyText><![CDATA[<div class="g12"><img src="/media/13054405/taste-of-slovenia.jpg" alt="Taste Of Slovenia" rel="879,452" /></div>
<div> </div>
<!--start left column-->
<div class="g12">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p><strong>The capital of <a data-udi="umb://document/eb90f98d70e84089a8cb145d8e46e049" href="/{localLink:umb://document/eb90f98d70e84089a8cb145d8e46e049}" title="Slovenia">Slovenia</a> and lying between the Alps and the Adriatic Sea, Ljubljana is one of central Europe's most attractive cities. Its vibrant centre is full of cultural and historical sights, including a 16th century castle and a medieval Old Town. Our Ljubljana hotels are conveniently located in the city centre, allowing you to stroll through this stunning city at leisure.</strong></p>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h3>Things to do in Ljubljana</h3>
<p> </p>
<p>With wonderful architecture and beautiful natural areas such as the Imperial Tivoli Park, Ljubljana, Slovenia is a compact and outdoor city, easily enjoyed by bike or on foot. There is an array of open-air bars and cafés lining the riverside, plus excellent theatres, museums and art galleries, a colourful, daily outdoor market and a Sunday flea market. The Ljubljana Summer Festival also brings world-class music to the city throughout July and August.</p>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h3>Taste of Slovenia - Recommended 2 Centre Combinations</h3>
<p>On this brand new seven night holiday, combine the charm and culture of the capital, Ljubljana for two nights with five nights, in either the stunning mountain resort of <a rel="noopener noreferrer" data-udi="umb://document/9b6cf6eac79541f5850e141e41a071ab" href="/{localLink:umb://document/9b6cf6eac79541f5850e141e41a071ab}" target="_blank" title="Kranjska Gora">Kranjska Gora</a>; the idyllic lakeside village of <a rel="noopener noreferrer" data-udi="umb://document/e0872feec9b24b8db1b30d83108b172e" href="/{localLink:umb://document/e0872feec9b24b8db1b30d83108b172e}" target="_blank" title="Lake Bled">Bled</a> or the Adriatic resort of <a rel="noopener noreferrer" data-udi="umb://document/3bc4cfb72cd34cab95d1aefb0455310e" href="/{localLink:umb://document/3bc4cfb72cd34cab95d1aefb0455310e}" target="_blank" title="Piran">Piran</a>. Departures from the UK are on Saturdays with a transfer included on Monday to your chosen second centre. City transfers and return airport transfers also included.</p>
<p>Set between the Alps and the Adriatic. Ljubljana is perhaps not so well known as other European cities but it is certainly one of the most attractive with wealth of cultural and historic attractions easily explored on foot or by public transport using the Resort Card (see below). During July and August the famous Summer Festival brings world – class music to the city. You can also combine Ljublijana with any other Slovenian resort for 3, 4 or 7 nights stays.</p>
<div style="columns: 100px 2; -webkit-columns: 100px 2; /* safari and chrome */-moz-columns: 100px 2;"></div>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h3>Taste of Slovenia Resort Card</h3>
<h2> </h2>
<p>The great value ‘Ljubljana City - Urbana Card’ can be purchased at all of our Ljubljana hotels and provides:</p>
<ul>
<li>Free transportation on public transport</li>
<li>Free admission to city sights &amp; museums</li>
<li>Free guided city tours</li>
<li>Free or discounted rates on bike hire, funicular &amp; tourist boats</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Please call our reservations team on 01483 371211 to book this holiday</h2>
</div>
</div>]]></bodyText>
